# WebSocket Protocol

## Request (client → server)

```json
{
  "mass": 28801,
  "flight_path": [
    { "action": "launch", "planet": "earth" },
    { "action": "land", "planet": "moon" }
  ]
}
```

## Response (server → client)

```json
{
  "total_fuel": 51898,
  "breakdown": [
    { "action": "launch", "planet": "earth", "fuel": 0 }
  ]
}
```

## Server

- Validate incoming payloads (positive mass, valid actions/planets, non-empty path).
- Call `fuel-core` for calculation; never implement formulas inline.
- Respond on every valid message.

## Client

- Maintain persistent WebSocket connection.
- Reconnect on disconnect with backoff.
- Send updated payload on every input change.
- Handle in-flight and error states in the UI.

WebSocket is the primary communication channel — no REST submit endpoint.
